  Queue behaviour
  - Files are added via drop or file picker (multiple at once)
  - Processed strictly in order — first-in, first-out
  - New files added while uploading are automatically picked up

  Per-file states
  - Pending → grey dot, waiting
  - Hashing X/Y chunks… → blue pulsing dot + blue progress bar
  - XX% · 2.1 MB/s · ETA 12s → indigo pulsing dot + purple progress bar
  - ✓ Complete → green dot, bar at 100%, row dims
  - ✕ Error: ... → red dot, error message inline
  - Aborted → dark dot, row dims out

  Resume logic (checked before every upload, no re-hash):
  1. Check localStorage for saved upload_id + chunk_hashes
  2. If found → GET /fs/upload-session/:id → get received_chunks[] → upload only missing
  3. If not found or session expired → hash all chunks → POST /fs/upload-session → upload all

  Controls
  - Upload button — starts the queue (disabled while running or no pending items)
  - Pause button — pauses between chunks (toggles to Resume, orange tint); active item finishes its current chunk first
  - ✕ Abort per file — immediately aborts active upload, calls DELETE /fs/upload-session/:id, clears localStorage, removes from queue; for
  complete/error items it just removes the row
  - Dest prefix input (default chttp2/) — auto mkdir -p before first upload to that prefix


